@startuml 35_swimlane_component_responsibilities
!theme plain
title DRE 3D Framework -- Swimlane Diagram: Component Responsibilities

|#E3F2FD|User & Frontend|
start
:User submits\nNL query;
:Chatbot UI\n(Databricks Apps)\nDisplays response;

|#E8F5E9|LangGraph Orchestration|
:LangGraph receives\nuser message;
:Route to appropriate\nagent based on intent;
:Manage session state\nacross agent calls;
:Aggregate agent\nresponses;
:Return structured\nresponse to UI;

|#C8E6C9|Intent Router Agent|
:Classify intent:\nREAD / WRITE / AMBIGUOUS;
:Extract entities:\ntable, column, check_type;
:Detect ambiguity\nand clarify;

|#DCEDC8|Retrieval Agent|
:Load CAG context\n(static catalogs);
:Execute CRAG retrieval\n(dynamic patterns);
:Evaluate confidence:\nHIGH/MEDIUM/LOW;
if (Confidence?) then (MEDIUM)
  :Rewrite query\nand retry;
else (HIGH)
  :Use retrieved context;
endif

|#E1BEE7|SQL Generator Agent|
:Generate SQL\ngrounded by\nCAG + CRAG context;
:Provide explanation\nfor generated SQL;

|#FFCDD2|Security Guard|
:Enforce SELECT-only;
:Block forbidden keywords:\nDROP, INSERT, DELETE;
:Detect injection patterns;
if (Security violation?) then (YES)
  :Reject SQL;
  stop
else (NO)
  :Pass to next layer;
endif

|#FFF9C4|Governance Layer|
:Query PII catalog;
:Check compliance\nrequirements;
:Determine approval level:\nOwner / PO+TL / DataGov;

|#BBDEFB|SQL Optimizer Agent|
:Query UC metadata\n(schema, partitions);
:Add partition filters;
:Optimize query plan;
:Estimate cost (DBU);

|#FFE082|Duplicate Detector|
:Vector search\nfor similar rules;
:LLM semantic\ncomparison;
if (Duplicate found?) then (YES)
  :Return existing rule;
  stop
else (NO)
  :Continue to validation;
endif

|#C5E1A5|SQL Validator|
:Rule-based:\nSyntax + schema checks;
:LLM-based:\nLogical validation;
if (Valid?) then (NO)
  :Reject SQL;
  stop
else (YES)
  :Pass to approval;
endif

|#F8BBD0|Approval Gateway|
if (PII or non-owner?) then (YES)
  :Route to PO/TL/DataGov;
  :Send Jira ticket\n+ Email;
  :Wait for approval\n(SLA: 48h);
else (NO - Owner)
  :Auto-approve;
endif
:INSERT rule to Delta\n(is_active based on approval);

|#E3F2FD|Unity Catalog Delta|
:Store rule in\nanomaly_check_config;
:Log in audit table;
:Update session log;

|#E3F2FD|User & Frontend|
:Display confirmation\nto user;
stop

note right
  <b>Interactive Flow Complete</b>
  Rule created and stored
  Approval routed via policy
end note

|#FFCDD2|D1 Detection (Workflow)|
start
:Cron schedule\nOR upstream job trigger;
:Read active rules\nfrom Delta;
:Load baselines\nfrom metrics table;
:Execute DQ checks:\n- Z-score\n- Null rate\n- Freshness\n- Drift;
if (Anomaly detected?) then (YES)
  :Write to\nDIGITAL_DATA_ANOMALIES;
  :Write to\nincident_context;
  :Send alert\n(Jira + Email);
  :Trigger D2 workflow;
else (NO)
  :Log PASS;
  stop
endif

|#F8BBD0|D2 Diagnosis (Workflow)|
:Read incident_context\n(status: PENDING);
:Classify signal:\nPipeline vs Data\nInfra vs Code;

|#FFF9C4|Evidence Retriever Agent|
:Retrieve job logs\n(Jobs API);
:Query Delta history\n(DESCRIBE HISTORY);
:Search runbooks\n(Confluence);
:Search code\n(GitHub);
:Query prior incidents\n(ITSM);
:RAG: Search incident_kb\n(vector search);

|#FFF8E1|Deployment Correlator|
:Query deployment_registry\n(recent changes);
:Correlate with\nincident timing;
:Identify code/config changes;

|#E1BEE7|Playbook Compiler Agent|
:LLM: Compile evidence\ninto playbook;
:Generate root cause\nanalysis;
:Generate prescription\n(fix recommendation);
:Write evidence_bundle\nto Delta;
:Update incident_context\n(READY_FOR_DEFLECTION);
:Trigger D3 workflow;

|#CE93D8|D3 Deflection (Workflow)|
:Read evidence_bundle\nfrom Delta;

|#FFF9C4|State Validator Agent|
:Verify corruption\nstill present;
if (Already resolved?) then (YES)
  :Mark RESOLVED_EXTERNALLY;
  stop
else (NO)
  :Continue to\ncircuit breaker;
endif

|#FFCDD2|Circuit Breaker Agent|
:Query remediation_policy;
:Check blast_radius;
:Check PII flag;
:Check fix risk;
if (High risk?) then (YES)
  :Route to Approval Gate;
else (NO - Auto-fix allowed)
  :Skip approval;
endif

|#F8BBD0|Approval Gate Agent|
:LLM: Format diagnostic\nsummary;
:Send Jira ticket\n+ Email;
:Wait for approval\n(SLA: 48h);

|#E1BEE7|Domain Executor Agent|
:Execute approved fix:\n- Rollback deployment\n- Schema migration\n- Pipeline restart\n- Data backfill;
:E2E verification\n(re-run checks);
if (Fix successful?) then (YES)
  :Mark RESOLVED;
else (NO)
  :Mark REMEDIATION_FAILED;
  :Escalate to L2 support;
  stop
endif

|#C8E6C9|Feedback Learner Agent|
:Update incident_kb\n(resolved case);
:Update baselines\n(feedback to D1);
:Calibrate policy\n(auto-fix eligibility);
:Send notification\nto user;
stop

legend right
  <b>Swimlane Diagram: Component Responsibilities</b>
  
  <b>Interactive Path (Top):</b>
  User → UI → LangGraph → Agents
  → Validation Pipeline (6 layers)
  → Approval Gateway → Delta
  
  <b>Async Path (Bottom):</b>
  D1 (Detection)
  → D2 (Diagnosis: Evidence + Playbook)
  → D3 (Deflection: Approval + Fix + Feedback)
  
  <b>Key Responsibilities by Component:</b>
  
  <b>User & Frontend:</b>
  - User interaction
  - Display responses
  
  <b>LangGraph Orchestration:</b>
  - Route intents
  - Manage state
  - Coordinate agents
  
  <b>Intent Router Agent:</b>
  - Classify READ/WRITE
  - Extract entities
  
  <b>Retrieval Agent:</b>
  - CAG (static)
  - CRAG (dynamic + confidence gate)
  
  <b>SQL Generator Agent:</b>
  - Generate grounded SQL
  
  <b>Security Guard:</b>
  - SELECT-only enforcement
  - Injection detection
  
  <b>Governance Layer:</b>
  - PII detection
  - Approval routing
  
  <b>SQL Optimizer Agent:</b>
  - Query optimization
  - Cost estimation
  
  <b>Duplicate Detector:</b>
  - Semantic similarity (RAG + LLM)
  
  <b>SQL Validator:</b>
  - Syntax + schema (rule)
  - Logic (LLM)
  
  <b>Approval Gateway:</b>
  - Policy-based routing
  - SLA enforcement
  
  <b>Unity Catalog Delta:</b>
  - Persistent storage
  - State management
  
  <b>D1 Detection:</b>
  - Execute DQ checks
  - Detect anomalies
  - Trigger D2
  
  <b>Evidence Retriever:</b>
  - Multi-source evidence
  - RAG from incident_kb
  
  <b>Deployment Correlator:</b>
  - Code/config correlation
  
  <b>Playbook Compiler:</b>
  - LLM reasoning
  - Root cause + prescription
  
  <b>State Validator:</b>
  - Verify corruption present
  
  <b>Circuit Breaker:</b>
  - Risk assessment
  - Policy enforcement
  
  <b>Approval Gate:</b>
  - Human-in-loop gate
  
  <b>Domain Executor:</b>
  - Automated remediation
  - Verification
  
  <b>Feedback Learner:</b>
  - Update knowledge base
  - Calibrate policy
  - Close loop to D1
  
  <b>Communication Patterns:</b>
  - Interactive: LangGraph state
  - Async: Delta tables + triggers
  - External: REST/MCP adapters
endlegend

@enduml
